abstract.gco:CharacterString: These data layers represent public land survey system (PLSS) corners for Sauk County, Wisconsin in 2018. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, "Sauk_PLSS_2018.gdb". The feature layers included in this geodatabase are "Sauk_PLSSCorners_2018", "Sauk_PLSSQuarterSection_2018", "Sauk_PLSSSection_2018", and "Sauk_PLSSTownship_2018". [PLSSCorners: The current control point on the surface of the earth and its associated current coordinate value, generally determined by a surveying process and used to define an extremity of a boundary.PLSSQuarterSection: The second division of the PLSS and commonly called a quarter section.PLSSSection: The first division of the PLSS and commonly called a section.PLSSTownship: In the Public Land Survey System a Township refers to a unit of land, that is nominally six miles on a side, usually containing 36 sections.]

purpose.gco:CharacterString: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [PLSSCorners: Sauk County Section Corners. PLSSQuarterSection: PLSS Quarter Sections. Broken down to Quarter Sections, Sixteenths, and Government Lots. PLSSSection: PLSS Section. PLSSTownship: PLSS Township.]
